Attributes._Description: "SubSSN may change after a Subscriber plug.  When this happens the lookup runs again.  We'd like to avoid this."
"If any entries are found the presentation is outside the UDF."

"Ok, this is screwy I know.  We need to replace a value from the claim with a value from the table.  Specifically, after a successful subscriber lookup we might replace the value in SubSSN with a value from the mem_info table.  This means, of course, a key field in the lookup changes.  Because of this the SL is no longer plugged.  My idea here is to use a unique key from the lookup to do the lookup again.  The same row that plugged before will plug and, in theory, the same SSN will plug again.  \015\012\015\012This sounds bad, and I suppose it is, but this is a rare case when the plugged value from the sub lookup differs from the SubSSN lookup *and* the SubSSN lookup returns more than one row."
